  "body": "If you want to see what the current-context for your client is, you can run\n`kubectl config view --minify`\nbut that shows you the full config associated with the current-context. If you want _just_ the current-context, you have to use a template\n`kubectl config view -o template --template='{{ index . \"current-context\" }}'`\nNot great ux. Should we add a command to view just the current-context? e.g.\n`kubectl config current`\n\ncc @ghodss, @deads2k, @bgrant0607 \n",
